      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading configurations, including at least two angulation offsets and two loading rates, with environmental controls documented.",
      "rationale": "All experimental testing was performed under a single standardized ASTM F1717 configuration (6-degree angulation, quasi-static 5 mm/min crosshead rate, ambient temperature). The protocol fully conforms to the ASTM standard and is widely accepted for regulatory submissions. Inter-laboratory reproducibility was confirmed with a coefficient of variation below 4% across the two sites, providing confidence in the experimental baseline."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably replicate experimental fixture geometry, loading point, and constraint conditions.",
      "rationale": "Fixture geometry digitized from engineering drawings and confirmed against laboratory photographs. Loading point and constraint conditions in FEA replicate the ASTM F1717 test frame to within 0.5 mm positional tolerance. Requirement level 3 is met."
