      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical performance requirements for pedicle screw constructs under compression-bending.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the primary regulatory QoIs for pedicle screw fatigue and static strength assessment per FDA guidance. These quantities are directly predictive of in vivo mechanical performance under physiological compression-bending loading. Requirement level 3 is met."
